    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>NIH AIDS Clinical Trials Information Service</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare 2 combination drug therapies in HIV-infected patients
      who have never received anti-HIV treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this open-label study antiretroviral-naive patients are randomized to one of two drug
      regimens:

      Arm I: 141W94 (amprenavir), 1592U89 (abacavir), and Combivir (3TC/AZT tablet). Arm II:
      Nelfinavir and Combivir.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
